ames but reinstated after the governing UIPM, led by 77-year-old German Klaus Schormann, decided the equestrian element would be replaced by obstacle racing post-Paris.\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9369989983545631, \"rank\": 0.045529614019472905, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9901540171091169, \"rank\": 0.009943890262627595, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sport\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"the initial list\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Los Angeles Games\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"the governing UIPM\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"post\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1062}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1068}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The coming change has caused ructions, with some athletes threatening to walk away but the sport hoping to appeal to a younger and more diverse audience already sold on popular obstacle course franchises.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1275, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The coming change\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"ructions\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"some athletes\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1128}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"a younger and more diverse audience\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"popular obstacle course franchises\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To continue our Olympic future we had to make that change,\\\" Britain's former world champion Jamie Cooke, who works with the Swiss team and is on the UIPM's athletes' committee, told Reuters.\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9934724158038387, \"rank\": 0.0065624675996739205, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cooke_(pentathlete)\", \"score\": 0.999997677670276, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jamie Cooke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cooke_(pentathlete)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cooke_(pentathlete)\"}, {\"begin\": 1402, \"end\": 1407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9995517601881763, \"rank\": 0.00023387272654644346, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 1427, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Internationale_de_Pentathlon_Moderne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UIPM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Internationale_de_Pentathlon_Moderne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Internationale_de_Pentathlon_Moderne\"}, {\"begin\": 1460, \"end\": 1467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999158717, \"rank\": 8.420787124115817e-11, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our Olympic future\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"that change\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1335}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What we have seen over the last year, year and a half now, is an acceptance.\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1546, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last year\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"an acceptance\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With Paris we know it will be that close of the chapter, it will be the end of the era - an era that saw us as one of the oldest Olympic sports and there is real tradition and pride in that.\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1554, \"end\": 1559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999877218, \"rank\": 1.2350600292774376e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the chapter\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"the era\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1635}, {\"ngram\": \"an era\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"the oldest Olympic sports\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"real tradition\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"pride\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we know we have to modernise.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We know that going forward this does provide us with a huge opportunity to capture a new audience, a new demographic and hopefully new athletes as we move forwards to make us really successful.\\\"\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1970, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge opportunity\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"a new audience\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"a new demographic and hopefully new athletes\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1919}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That may be wishful thinking, with the sport's name carrying more than a touch of irony given its decades-long battle to stay relevant.\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 2107, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wishful thinking\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's name\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"a touch\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"irony\", \"from\": 2054, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"its decades-long battle\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Enthusiasts point to continuous evolution since its debut in 1912 when the, possibly apocryphal, creation story states that Olympics founder Baron Pierre de Coubertin wanted an event to highlight the skills needed by a 19th-century cavalry officer attacking a castle.\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2256, \"end\": 2275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Enthusiasts\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2120}, {\"ngram\": \"continuous evolution\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2150}, {\"ngram\": \"its debut\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"creation story\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2220}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"the skills\", \"from\": 2305, \"to\": 2315}, {\"ngram\": \"a 19th-century cavalry officer\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2356}, {\"ngram\": \"a castle\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2375}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The firearms and swords are now laser pistols and electric epees and, in four years' time, it will be courses instead of horses.\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The firearms\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2390}, {\"ngram\": \"swords\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2401}, {\"ngram\": \"laser pistols\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2423}, {\"ngram\": \"electric epees\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2442}, {\"ngram\": \"four years' time\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2467}, {\"ngram\": \"courses\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2487}, {\"ngram\": \"horses\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether that is enough to raise the profile more than every four years remains to be seen.\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2598, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the profile\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2551}, {\"ngram\": \"every four years\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2578}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris at least, the horses will go out in style - saddled up for one last ride in the gardens of the Chateau de Versailles, the palatial home of the 17th century 'Sun King' Louis XIV.\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2603, \"end\": 2608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999877218, \"rank\": 1.2350600292774376e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2704, \"end\": 2725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chateau de Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}, {\"begin\": 2776, \"end\": 2785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3903278340197611e-12, \"text\": \"Louis XIV\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"dbped